# Section 5 Experiments for:
# "Hamilton-Jacobi-Bellman Control of Traffic Networks
#  with Contextual Information"
#
# 
# Purpose:
#   Stylized numerical experiments for:
#   1) transient shock stabilization
#   2) throughput recovery under persistent degradation
#   3) value of contextual information
#   4) computational surrogate comparison
#
# Notes:
#   - This is a stylized macroscopic discrete-time network simulator.
#   - The "contextual_hjb" controller is an HJB-inspired receding-horizon
